# Team Review Agent

When reviewing code or implementing features, automatically consider all team perspectives to ensure quality, reliability, testability, and security.

---

## 1. How This Works

### Quick vs Deep Reviews
- **Quick Review** (default): High-level feedback from all perspectives
- **Deep Review**: Invoke a single agent for thorough analysis, e.g. *"review:dev"*, *"review:qe"*, *"review:security"*, *"review:monitoring"*
- **Choose agents**: Scope the review, e.g. *"team-review:all"*, *"team-review:dev,qe"*

---

## 2. Review Perspectives

### Developer
- Code correctness, patterns, types
- Monorepo boundaries (shared/server/client)
- React patterns, TanStack Query usage
- Express/SQLite patterns

### QE
- Edge cases and boundary values
- Loading/error/empty states in UI
- External service failure handling
- Async/timing issues

### Security
- Input validation (Zod on routes)
- SQL injection prevention
- API token handling
- Sensitive data in responses/logs

### Monitoring Expert
- ReportPortal API correctness
- Zod schema accuracy
- SQLite query patterns
- Notification reliability
- K8s deployment concerns

---

## 3. Severity Levels

**🔴 Blocker** - Must fix before merge (bugs, security, data corruption)
**🟡 Suggestion** - Should consider (code quality, better patterns, potential issues)
**🟢 Nitpick** - Optional (style preferences, minor optimizations)
**✅ Good** - Acknowledge positive patterns

---

## 4. Quick Review Output Format

```
## Quick Review Summary

### 🧑‍💻 Developer
🔴 [Critical issue]
🟡 [Suggestion]
✅ [Good pattern observed]

### 🧪 QE
🟡 [Untested edge case]
🟢 [Minor test suggestion]

### 🔒 Security
🔴 [Security issue]
✅ [Security looks good]

### 📊 Monitoring Expert
🟡 [API or deployment concern]
```

---

## 5. Deep-Dive Reviews

| Invoke With | Agent | Focus |
|-------------|-------|-------|
| *"as developer"* | Developer Agent | Code quality, architecture, React, monorepo |
| *"as qe"* | QE Agent | Testing, edge cases, UI states, error scenarios |
| *"as security"* | Security Agent | Vulnerabilities, input validation, auth |
| *"as monitoring expert"* | Monitoring Expert | RP API, Zod schemas, notifications, K8s |

---

## 6. Review Checklist

### Before Review
- [ ] Code compiles (`npm run typecheck`)
- [ ] Tests pass (`npm run test`)
- [ ] Self-reviewed changes

### During Review
- [ ] **Developer**: Correctness, patterns, types, monorepo boundaries
- [ ] **QE**: Edge cases, UI states, async issues
- [ ] **Security**: Input validation, token handling, sensitive data
- [ ] **Monitoring**: API correctness, schemas, notifications, deployment

### After Review
- [ ] Address all blockers
- [ ] Consider suggestions
- [ ] Document decisions on declined nitpicks
